  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across key boundary conditions; a screening sensitivity study was conducted internally to rank input variability, with results summarized in the UQ report narrative. Dominant drivers were identified verbally as inlet flow rate and rotational speed, though no formal structured sensitivity analysis record has been linked to this package.",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-rh-criterion",
