    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scoping. Uncertainty quantification has been performed and confirms the RH < 1 acceptance criterion is satisfied across the full input uncertainty distribution. A screening sensitivity study was conducted and its findings are summarized in the UQ report narrative, identifying inlet flow rate and rotational speed as dominant NIH drivers. The model is judged credible for the intended COU of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Decision: Accepted for regulatory submission.",
